-[man 4] Call it a day.

01:59.786 --> 02:01.204
[Cosmo] Lucas, we can
just come back another day.

02:01.287 --> 02:02.455
[man 3] Let's call it, man.

02:03.206 --> 02:05.041
I'm not leaving till I get this.

02:05.124 --> 02:06.584
[man 4] You've got one more,
and we're out of here.

02:06.668 --> 02:07.877
[crowd chattering]

02:08.962 --> 02:10.421
-[thuds]
-[man] Hey, Lucas.

02:10.505 --> 02:13.049
[dramatic music playing]

02:14.342 --> 02:14.759
[man]<i> Lucas.</i>

02:14.843 --> 02:16.427
[indistinct chatter]

02:16.511 --> 02:17.762
For real.

02:17.846 --> 02:19.889
Dude, yo, he's done today.

02:19.973 --> 02:21.558
Hey, put the camera down
and help us.

02:21.641 --> 02:23.643
-Hold on.
-Lucas?

02:25.019 --> 02:27.313
-You all right, bro?
-[muffled] Lucas.

02:27.397 --> 02:28.648
[high-pitched ringing]

02:28.731 --> 02:30.733
-[ominous music]
-[indistinct chatter]

02:30.817 --> 02:32.443
[Jane]<i> Lucas!</i>

02:46.040 --> 02:47.834
[Jane]<i> Do you want some water</i>
<i>or tea or some oatmeal?</i>

02:47.917 --> 02:50.169
[Lucas]
<i>No, I'm good, thank you.</i>

02:50.253 --> 02:51.296
[Jane]<i> You sure you don't</i>
<i>want some oatmeal?</i>

02:56.259 --> 02:57.343
What's up, Mom?

02:58.678 --> 03:00.305
