-Don't do that, Lucas.

03:16.863 --> 03:19.282
[Lucas]<i> You want me to be</i>
<i>more sad or less sad?</i>

03:19.365 --> 03:21.367
<i>I feel like</i>
<i>the second somebody dies,</i>

03:21.451 --> 03:25.622
everybody acts like they were
some saint or something.

03:25.705 --> 03:29.125
You never had anything good
to say about him growing up.

03:29.208 --> 03:31.586
Like, if we even
talked about him.

03:31.669 --> 03:36.549
You know, when you were a kid,
we explained things to you
in kid terms,

03:36.633 --> 03:39.177
<i>but it's not</i>
<i>that black and white.</i>

03:39.260 --> 03:41.679
<i>There was so much more</i>
<i>to the story than you know.</i>

03:41.763 --> 03:43.348
[Lucas]<i> Okay.</i>

03:50.063 --> 03:50.229
How'd he die?

03:53.608 --> 03:54.984
Lung cancer.

04:01.574 --> 04:03.409
Nice.

04:06.245 --> 04:09.999
Your Uncle Tommy
went to the estate lawyer.

04:11.125 --> 04:13.044
And, um, your dad
left everything to you.

04:13.127 --> 04:15.964
Oh, my God,
the fucking deadbeat dude.

04:16.047 --> 04:18.174
I don't want any of his stuff.

04:18.257 --> 04:21.803
-Can you please just ask
Uncle Tommy to take care of it?
-No.

04:21.886 --> 04:23.388
All of the apartments
are in your name.

04:28.935 --> 04:30.478
What apartments?

04:33.231 --> 04:35.817
[funky music playing]

05:13.813 --> 05:16.315
[music continues]

06:43.069 --> 06:44.445
[engine shuts off]

06:44.529 --> 06:45.530
[car door shuts]

06:50.451 --> 06:51.536
[light music plays]

07:17.395 --> 07:18.437
[keys jingling]

08:17.413 --> 08:20.291
[door hinges creak]

08:43.814 --> 08:44.690
[lighter clicks]

08:48.736 --> 08:50.905
[exhales]

08:50.988 --> 08:51.447
