[chuckles]

14:28.993 --> 14:30.286
[Lucas] Oh, boy, all right.

14:30.369 --> 14:32.454
-[woman] I knew you would.
-Get on.

14:32.538 --> 14:32.830
[woman] Okay, ready?

14:35.374 --> 14:36.917
Pull me.

14:37.001 --> 14:38.627
-Come on, pull me.
-No.

14:38.711 --> 14:40.212
Pull me!
[laughs]

14:41.880 --> 14:45.342
Faster.
Come on, pull me, bitch!

14:45.426 --> 14:46.885
[laughs] Come on.

14:46.969 --> 14:48.804
Come on! Faster!

14:48.887 --> 14:51.265
Faster!
Okay, now let go, let go.

14:51.348 --> 14:52.975
I'm doing it!
[laughs]

14:53.058 --> 14:55.269
[squealing, grunts]

14:58.355 --> 15:00.649
Uh, just keep it--
keep it elevated.

15:00.733 --> 15:02.776
I broke my wrist
a bunch of times.

15:02.860 --> 15:04.361
-You just gotta, like...
-Can we please talk about
something else?

15:04.445 --> 15:06.989
Like, anything else.

15:07.072 --> 15:09.325
-Yeah.
Yeah, yeah, sorry.
-Thank you.

15:15.122 --> 15:18.292
So, uh, what do you do for work?

15:20.085 --> 15:22.963
I, um-- I sell vintage.

15:23.047 --> 15:24.173
-Sell vintage?
-Mm-hmm.

15:24.256 --> 15:27.051
Yeah, like,
I buy vintage clothes
and then I sell them.

15:27.134 --> 15:31.138
Unless I really like them.
Then I keep 'em for myself.

15:31.221 --> 15:36.143
So you basically shop
for yourself for a living,
as a job?

15:38.062 --> 15:38.437
[laughs]

15:38.520 --> 15:41.065
Kind of, I guess.

15:41.857 --> 15:42.066
That's cool.

15:44.234 --> 15:45.110
That's awesome.

15:46.987 --> 15:49.239
You know,
you don't have to stay here.

15:49.323 --> 15:50.949
You can-- you can leave.

15:51.283 --> 15:53.327
I know.

15:54.203 --> 15:56.705
-[crickets chirping]
-[dog barking]

15:56.789 --> 15:59.458
[indistinct chatter]

16:03.003 --> 16:04.755
[faucet handle squeaking]

16:12.221 --> 16:13.806
Oh! What the fuck?

16:13.889 --> 16:15.432
God damn it!

16:15.516 --> 16:16.558
Ah, fuck!

16:16.642 --> 16:18.519
Fuck, fuck me, Jesus!

16:23.315 --> 16:25.109
Shit.

16:26.276 --> 16:28.278
Help! Hey!

16:29.655 --> 16:31.532
You have no experience
with plumbing,

16:31.615 --> 16:34.576
but you thought
you would just go ahead
and twist some valves?

16:35.160 --> 16:38.163
All right, go ahead.

16:38.247 --> 16:40.541
Twist the new valve,
open it up.

16:43.335 --> 16:45.921
-[valve handle squeaks]
-All right, now try the water.

16:49.091 --> 16:50.092
[man] There you go!

16:50.175 --> 16:51.635
See?

16:51.719 --> 16:54.346
You really do work better alone.

16:54.805 --> 16:56.598
Pretty much.

16:57.266 --> 16:59.643
Ah, it's an old building.

16:59.727 --> 17:02.187
