17:51.737 --> 17:54.573
-Uncle Tommy?
-Yes!

17:54.656 --> 17:56.617
I thought you were gonna
kill me with that thing, man.

17:56.700 --> 17:58.994
-You should knock next time.
-I-- I just...

18:00.162 --> 18:01.163
[chuckles]

18:01.747 --> 18:02.998
It's me.
[chuckles]

18:03.081 --> 18:06.627
-[light music playing]
-[no audible dialogue]

18:22.267 --> 18:24.061
[Tommy] It's a nice
old building, you know.

18:24.144 --> 18:26.730
I mean, no rent control.
[knocking]

18:26.814 --> 18:27.564
-[man] Yo, come in.
-[Tommy] Hey, hey!

18:27.648 --> 18:30.025
Hey, there he is!

18:31.318 --> 18:33.529
-[grunts]
-[Tommy] How are ya?

18:33.612 --> 18:35.906
-How are ya?
-Captain. [chuckling]

18:35.989 --> 18:37.032
So...

18:38.283 --> 18:39.201
What's new, Tom?

18:40.828 --> 18:42.329
A lot.

18:42.412 --> 18:44.248
A whole lot of shaking going on.

18:47.000 --> 18:50.546
Sammy Stein, Luke.

18:50.629 --> 18:54.967
This is the best of the best
of property law.

18:56.134 --> 18:57.553
Ooh.

18:57.636 --> 18:59.137
-Hey.
-Hey.

18:59.221 --> 19:01.682
-How's it going?
-[chuckling]

19:01.765 --> 19:04.434
Yeah, old Sammy here,

19:04.518 --> 19:07.396
he got me out of a jam or two
back in the day.

19:07.479 --> 19:11.191
-[Lucas] Yeah?
-Old IRS wanted to take
everything from me.

19:13.110 --> 19:15.320
The shirt off my back.

19:15.404 --> 19:17.406
-In fact, every shirt.
-Fuck the IRS.

19:17.489 --> 19:20.325
[men chuckling]

19:20.409 --> 19:21.577
[Tommy laughing]
He always says that.

19:21.660 --> 19:24.037
[Sammy grunts]

19:24.121 --> 19:25.622
So, I just got off the phone
with the legal team

19:25.706 --> 19:28.584
at Innovation Holdings,

19:28.667 --> 19:30.502
and the offer
is still on the table.

19:30.586 --> 19:33.130
Of course it is.
[chuckles]

19:33.213 --> 19:35.424
You should have seen me
selling these people.

19:35.507 --> 19:37.926
I was like fucking golden.

19:38.010 --> 19:39.761
[Sammy] All right,
so here's the contract.

19:39.845 --> 19:41.805
Now, I looked this over
and it's solid.

19:41.889 --> 19:43.932
I mean,
this is a really good deal.

19:44.808 --> 19:49.146
But all you need to do now
is you sign.

19:52.190 --> 19:54.693
You-- you wanted me
to sign it like right now?

19:58.030 --> 19:59.239
Why the hell else
you think we're here?

20:01.241 --> 20:03.577
You said you wanted
to sell, right?

20:08.040 --> 20:11.335
-[waves crashing]
-[seagulls cawing]

20:16.673 --> 20:18.300
[Kieffer] Hey, bro,
seriously, it doesn't matter

20:18.383 --> 20:21.470
if it's a dude, if it's a chick,
if it's some kind of animal,

20:21.553 --> 20:24.014
I don't know, just--
I just wanna see my bro
get his pee-pee touched.

20:24.097 --> 20:25.891
-Like, for real.
-[laughing]

20:25.974 --> 20:28.018
-You know, like...
-What are you even
talking about, bro?

20:28.101 --> 20:30.854
-Like, I just wanna
see you happy.
-[laughs]

20:30.938 --> 20:32.314
For real, you come to LA,
you're all like moody and shit.

20:32.397 --> 20:36.443
I don't know, like, I just--
I mean, for real, like...

20:36.526 --> 20:37.653
Like, whatever happened
with you and Juliet?

20:38.570 --> 20:41.990
