1:12:23.338 --> 1:12:25.090
[Lucas]
I'm selling the apartments.

1:12:26.216 --> 1:12:27.968
-To who?
-[Lucas] I don't give a shit.

1:12:28.052 --> 1:12:30.512
I don't know, anybody.

1:12:30.596 --> 1:12:32.556
My Uncle Tommy's
got some people lined up.

1:12:32.639 --> 1:12:34.224
I don't fucking know.

1:12:34.308 --> 1:12:36.602
-Is this about that chick?
-[Lucas] No, it's not about--

1:12:36.685 --> 1:12:38.937
You guys seemed super happy
last time we hung out.

1:12:39.021 --> 1:12:40.314
God, no it's not
about the fucking chick.

1:12:47.362 --> 1:12:49.448
I mean, like,
maybe part of it is.

1:12:52.868 --> 1:12:54.953
-[sighs]
-A'ight. Yo.

1:12:56.080 --> 1:12:57.289
This stays between us.

1:12:59.625 --> 1:13:02.586
The last year
I almost quit the team.

1:13:02.669 --> 1:13:05.297
Can we just not talk
about skateboarding
for like two seconds?

1:13:07.549 --> 1:13:08.801
-It's a metaphor, Lucas.
-Oh, God.

1:13:08.884 --> 1:13:10.969
Hey, just listen.

1:13:13.514 --> 1:13:14.431
I put so much pressure
on myself.

1:13:15.390 --> 1:13:18.977
You know, like, just--
it adds up, bro.

1:13:19.061 --> 1:13:20.646
Like, it just becomes too much.

1:13:20.729 --> 1:13:22.398
It's not fun anymore.

1:13:24.274 --> 1:13:24.399
Yeah.

1:13:26.318 --> 1:13:28.362
Yeah, so I just peaced out.

1:13:28.445 --> 1:13:31.365
You know, I didn't even tell
anybody where I was going.

1:13:31.448 --> 1:13:33.784
I just bounced out of town
for like three weeks.

1:13:33.867 --> 1:13:35.119
Didn't even take my phone.

1:13:36.120 --> 1:13:38.455
But when I came back,
everything was fine.

1:13:40.415 --> 1:13:43.210
Damn, you didn't even invite me.

1:13:44.545 --> 1:13:47.631
Hey, all I'm saying is sometimes

1:13:47.714 --> 1:13:50.425
you just gotta like
take a step back.

1:13:51.593 --> 1:13:53.137
For real, Lucas.

1:13:53.220 --> 1:13:54.471
[Lucas] Mm.

1:13:54.555 --> 1:13:56.348
Oh, shit, eh.

1:13:56.431 --> 1:13:57.850
You're the type of dude
who'll kill at whatever
you do.

1:13:57.933 --> 1:14:00.352
[chuckles]

1:14:00.435 --> 1:14:02.271
Unless it's being a landlord.
Then you're fucked.

1:14:02.354 --> 1:14:04.439
[all laugh]

1:14:04.523 --> 1:14:07.359
[light music playing]

1:14:59.536 --> 1:15:02.664
[Jane on phone]
<i>Hey, you're up early.</i>

1:15:04.875 --> 1:15:08.086
Um, yeah.

1:15:09.296 --> 1:15:10.714
<i>Are you okay?</i>

1:15:11.131 --> 1:15:13.217
I mean...

1:15:17.054 --> 1:15:18.680
no, I'm not.

1:15:21.183 --> 1:15:22.559
<i>You're safe, though,</i>
<i>right now, right?</i>

1:15:24.978 --> 1:15:26.355
Yeah, I'm safe.

1:15:35.239 --> 1:15:36.365
Mom...

1:15:41.370 --> 1:15:42.579
I know you kept him from me.

1:15:54.758 --> 1:15:58.262
I should have let your father
see you more.

1:16:00.097 --> 1:16:01.765
I'm so sorry, honey.

1:16:04.851 --> 1:16:05.769
I messed up.

1:16:07.062 --> 1:16:07.604
I messed up bad.

1:16:10.148 --> 1:16:12.234
I was trying to protect you,
but I ended up hurting you more

1:16:12.317 --> 1:16:14.569
by not letting him see you.

1:16:19.366 --> 1:16:21.076
[sighs]

1:16:22.869 --> 1:16:24.288
Your dad...

1:16:26.373 --> 1:16:27.708
total idiot.

1:16:29.251 --> 1:16:32.671
But he cared about you.
He did.

1:16:39.344 --> 1:16:42.597
<i>Parents,</i>
<i>we're-- we're just kids</i>
<i>who somehow got old.</i>

1:17:09.833 --> 1:17:10.709
Where do we go from here?

1:17:10.792 --> 1:17:13.420
-[water stops]
-[Lucas] What the fuck, dude?

1:17:13.503 --> 1:17:15.255
-I'm naked, get out.
-Well, come on.

1:17:15.339 --> 1:17:16.923
What are you doing?

1:17:17.007 --> 1:17:20.218
The buyers, man, the buyers,
they pulled out.

1:17:20.302 --> 1:17:23.639
Look, Uncle Tommy,
at first I really appreciated
you helping me out...

1:17:25.932 --> 1:17:28.352
but it's starting to seem
pretty obvious

1:17:28.435 --> 1:17:31.438
you're like desperate for money.

1:17:34.524 --> 1:17:35.734
I mean, what's up, man?

1:17:36.318 --> 1:17:38.695
I'm in a lot of debt.

1:17:41.031 --> 1:17:43.575
I don't even know how I'm gonna
make this month's mortgages.

1:17:45.786 --> 1:17:46.995
I have no idea.

1:17:48.080 --> 1:17:48.622
I was counting...

1:17:52.042 --> 1:17:53.251
Forget it.

1:17:54.920 --> 1:17:57.798
Maybe I can lend you some money
from the apartments.

1:18:00.884 --> 1:18:02.552
Till you get on your feet.

1:18:02.636 --> 1:18:03.845
Would that help?

1:18:07.015 --> 1:18:08.100
Huh?

1:18:09.184 --> 1:18:10.644
Yes, yes.

1:18:11.853 --> 1:18:12.187
That would be great.

1:18:12.270 --> 1:18:14.940
And, I mean...

1:18:15.023 --> 1:18:17.692
there's also like 30,000
for the car

1:18:17.776 --> 1:18:21.071
and, uh, 10,000 for the boat.

1:18:21.154 --> 1:18:23.657
Yeah, I can't do that, man.
I'm sorry.

1:18:26.368 --> 1:18:28.662
You're a good man, Lucas.

1:18:32.541 --> 1:18:34.793
Being an adult sucks.

1:18:34.876 --> 1:18:36.503
-Yeah.
-[chuckles]

1:18:37.796 --> 1:18:40.674
It's, uh-- it does blow.

1:18:42.384 --> 1:18:44.052
Hey, look, I don't wanna
start any shit.

1:18:44.136 --> 1:18:46.680
I just wanted to say
that I'm sorry.

1:18:52.227 --> 1:18:53.311
Okay.

1:18:59.067 --> 1:19:00.819
Come with me.

1:19:00.902 --> 1:19:02.821
What?

1:19:02.904 --> 1:19:04.156
No. Where?

1:19:04.239 --> 1:19:06.700
It'll be like our version
of<i> The Graduate.</i>

1:19:10.537 --> 1:19:12.706
I'm getting married in ten days.

1:19:12.789 --> 1:19:16.001
Ah, yeah,
it's gonna take awhile.

1:19:16.084 --> 1:19:18.003
Probably should just like
call the whole thing off.

1:19:18.086 --> 1:19:18.712
It's not funny, Lucas.

1:19:20.297 --> 1:19:22.257
I can't go with you.

1:19:25.469 --> 1:19:27.053
I mean, of course you can.

1:19:30.932 --> 1:19:32.768
But you don't want to.

1:19:32.851 --> 1:19:35.187
And that's what I came here
to find out.

1:19:36.104 --> 1:19:38.565
Part of me
really wants to, but I...

1:19:40.734 --> 1:19:40.775
I won't.

1:19:44.362 --> 1:19:46.156
Whatever happened
to the whole "live free,

1:19:46.239 --> 1:19:48.116
follow your dreams,
artist girl" shit, huh?

1:19:48.200 --> 1:19:51.411
Maybe I was just full of shit.

1:19:53.788 --> 1:19:54.789
Maybe I am just full of shit.

1:19:59.294 --> 1:20:00.795
You are so intense, Lucas.

1:20:03.507 --> 1:20:04.883
And I-- I thought...

1:20:06.301 --> 1:20:08.553
I thought I knew
what I wanted, but I just...

1:20:10.972 --> 1:20:12.849
I don't.

1:20:12.933 --> 1:20:15.936
Look, the only reason
you think everything's fine
all of the time

1:20:16.019 --> 1:20:20.106
is because he doesn't
think about anything
in a real way, ever.

1:20:20.190 --> 1:20:23.568
It's just like
some bullshit illusion.

1:20:26.029 --> 1:20:30.492
Maybe I'd rather
live in some bullshit,
comfortable illusion

1:20:30.575 --> 1:20:31.868
than some dark version
of reality.

1:20:34.496 --> 1:20:36.248
Did you ever think about that?

1:20:38.291 --> 1:20:41.169
I know that you think
that I'm your answer,

1:20:42.337 --> 1:20:43.922
but I'm-- I'm not.

1:20:47.008 --> 1:20:50.220
You know that whole thing
that, like,

1:20:50.303 --> 1:20:53.807
"you can't love somebody
unless you love yourself" thing?

1:20:58.353 --> 1:21:01.147
I mean, it's bullshit.

1:21:07.612 --> 1:21:10.115
Being there for somebody else
when you're down,

1:21:10.198 --> 1:21:10.907
that's fucking real love.

1:21:15.954 --> 1:21:18.873
So, why'd you go
on that road trip with me?

1:21:25.630 --> 1:21:25.922
I needed it.

1:21:29.551 --> 1:21:32.262
Just... something different.

1:21:36.099 --> 1:21:38.476
And you seemed like
a lot of fun.

1:21:40.895 --> 1:21:41.855
Well...

1:21:44.399 --> 1:21:44.858
surprise.

1:21:49.738 --> 1:21:49.904
Yeah.

1:21:52.282 --> 1:21:55.243
[light music playing]

1:22:12.761 --> 1:22:14.846
[no audible dialogue]

1:22:39.579 --> 1:22:39.996
[Lucas]<i> I can't do it.</i>

1:22:45.335 --> 1:22:47.253
Alone.

1:22:49.297 --> 1:22:51.257
I'm-- I'm keeping
the apartments,

1:22:51.341 --> 1:22:53.301
but, uh, I can't do it
without you.

1:22:53.385 --> 1:22:55.845
What's this?

1:22:56.805 --> 1:22:59.849
[chuckles]
You know that this
doesn't legally bind anything.

1:22:59.933 --> 1:23:00.934
Yeah, I know.

1:23:01.017 --> 1:23:03.311
It's more of a symbolic thing.

1:23:03.395 --> 1:23:04.729
I was gonna ask
Uncle Tommy to help me

1:23:04.813 --> 1:23:07.607
with his lawyer
create something,

1:23:07.691 --> 1:23:10.568
but I'm pretty sure
he's one of those legal shield
scam artists, so.

1:23:10.652 --> 1:23:12.696
[laughs] Yeah.

1:23:12.779 --> 1:23:16.741
I know, it was, uh,
the best I could do.

1:23:18.326 --> 1:23:19.244
I'll see you around, Frank.

1:23:19.327 --> 1:23:21.746
Hey, Baby Face.

1:23:25.041 --> 1:23:26.376
Be well, my friend.

1:23:54.028 --> 1:23:55.447
[Augusto]<i> Hey, Lucas.</i>

1:23:57.157 --> 1:24:00.577
<i>If you're listening to this,</i>
<i>I'm probably dead.</i>

1:24:02.412 --> 1:24:03.621
<i>God...</i>

1:24:04.247 --> 1:24:06.332
<i>when did I get so old?</i>

1:24:08.042 --> 1:24:13.131
<i>I don't know if you're ever</i>
<i>really ready to die,</i>

1:24:13.214 --> 1:24:18.261
<i>but, uh, maybe that means</i>
<i>you've always been</i>
<i>ready to die.</i>

1:24:20.305 --> 1:24:24.642
<i>Anyways, I wish</i>
<i>things were different.</i>

1:24:24.726 --> 1:24:28.897
<i>I just wish we had</i>
<i>a chance to just...</i>

1:24:29.647 --> 1:24:32.650
<i>hang out more, you know?</i>

1:24:36.112 --> 1:24:39.324
<i>I used to worry about you.</i>

1:24:39.407 --> 1:24:41.451
<i>A lot.</i>

1:24:42.452 --> 1:24:45.246
<i>But, uh, honestly,</i>

1:24:45.330 --> 1:24:47.165
<i>I'm not worried</i>
<i>about you, Lucas.</i>

1:24:47.248 --> 1:24:49.709
<i>You always had a drive</i>
<i>for something more,</i>

1:24:49.793 --> 1:24:53.713
<i>and I think that's a gift.</i>

1:24:53.797 --> 1:24:58.176
<i>Just don't be so hard</i>
<i>on yourself all the time.</i>

1:24:58.259 --> 1:25:02.347
<i>Jesus Christ,</i>
<i>you drove us crazy.</i>

1:25:02.430 --> 1:25:04.933
[chuckles]<i> Locking yourself up</i>
<i>in the skate park bathroom.</i>

1:25:05.016 --> 1:25:11.272
<i>But life or death</i>
<i>isn't life either.</i>

1:25:13.525 --> 1:25:16.027
<i>I think you get that</i>
<i>from your mom.</i>

1:25:16.110 --> 1:25:21.533
<i>She's driven by</i>
<i>the what-ifs of the world.</i>

1:25:23.076 --> 1:25:25.411
<i>The only way I know</i>
<i>how to operate</i>

1:25:25.495 --> 1:25:28.498
<i>is by the what-is.</i>

1:25:28.581 --> 1:25:31.709
[light music playing]

1:25:31.793 --> 1:25:34.546
<i>I don't blame her, though.</i>

1:25:34.629 --> 1:25:38.758
<i>I do have to give her</i>
<i>some major props.</i>

1:25:38.842 --> 1:25:40.718
<i>Jane...</i>

1:25:40.802 --> 1:25:42.887
<i>now that's a woman.</i>

1:25:42.971 --> 1:25:47.725
<i>Deep down,</i>
<i>a real, tough bitch.</i>

1:25:47.809 --> 1:25:54.482
<i>In the most loving and</i>
<i>amazingly unapologetic way</i>
<i>possible.</i>

1:25:54.566 --> 1:25:57.735
<i>She did what she had to do</i>
<i>to take care of you.</i>

1:25:57.819 --> 1:26:01.114
<i>I respect her for that.</i>

1:26:01.197 --> 1:26:04.534
<i>I think I always played</i>

1:26:04.617 --> 1:26:07.996
<i>the good cop</i>
<i>to her bad cop.</i>

1:26:08.079 --> 1:26:09.914
<i>And it wasn't fair to her.</i>

1:26:09.998 --> 1:26:12.250
<i>She got fed up with it.</i>

1:26:12.333 --> 1:26:14.252
<i>Things changed.</i>

1:26:14.335 --> 1:26:15.295
<i>I let it happen.</i>

1:26:15.378 --> 1:26:20.967
<i>I just wish I-- I knew</i>
<i>how to tell you that.</i>

1:26:24.554 --> 1:26:25.805
<i>So, um...</i>

1:26:25.889 --> 1:26:28.892
[clicks tongue, sighs]

1:26:28.975 --> 1:26:30.727
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

1:26:34.355 --> 1:26:37.192
<i>You know, you're getting</i>
<i>to be the age</i>

1:26:37.275 --> 1:26:39.569
<i>when I became a dad.</i>

1:26:40.695 --> 1:26:42.155
<i>Weird, right?</i>

1:26:43.489 --> 1:26:45.533
<i>Gonna be honest here.</i>

1:26:45.617 --> 1:26:47.952
<i>I never thought I wanted kids.</i>

1:26:48.036 --> 1:26:50.955
<i>And, man, I tell you,</i>

1:26:51.039 --> 1:26:53.750
<i>it is not a conversation</i>
<i>you wanna have</i>

1:26:53.833 --> 1:26:55.752
<i>with a pregnant woman.</i>

1:26:55.835 --> 1:26:58.546
<i>That definitely bit me</i>
<i>in the ass.</i>

1:27:00.048 --> 1:27:03.134
<i>What tore me up</i>
<i>is after you were born,</i>

1:27:03.217 --> 1:27:04.969
<i>I still didn't want a kid.</i>

1:27:06.095 --> 1:27:10.433
<i>But I-- I wanted Lucas.</i>

1:27:15.396 --> 1:27:19.400
<i>When you were a kid</i>
<i>and I started skating with you,</i>

1:27:19.484 --> 1:27:22.987
<i>I fell in love with it</i>
<i>because I finally found</i>

1:27:23.071 --> 1:27:26.032
<i>a language to speak with you.</i>

1:27:26.115 --> 1:27:29.827
<i>But you learn other languages.</i>

1:27:29.911 --> 1:27:34.374
<i>And, uh, with the apartments,</i>
<i>they're important.</i>

1:27:34.457 --> 1:27:39.128
<i>Not because of the cash</i>
<i>or superficial value,</i>

1:27:39.212 --> 1:27:42.465
<i>but because I wanted</i>
<i>to leave you something</i>

1:27:42.548 --> 1:27:44.801
<i>that you could use.</i>

1:27:44.884 --> 1:27:48.179
<i>Something you could have</i>
<i>as a man, you know.</i>

1:27:49.305 --> 1:27:51.933
-[light music]
-[no audible dialogue]

1:27:52.016 --> 1:27:55.687
[Augusto]
<i>I'm not gonna tell you</i>
<i>how to manage it</i>

1:27:55.770 --> 1:27:58.356
<i>or to even manage it at all,</i>

1:27:58.439 --> 1:28:00.692
<i>but there's definitely</i>
<i>some things</i>

1:28:00.775 --> 1:28:02.235
<i>worth learning</i>
<i>from the tenants.</i>

1:28:02.318 --> 1:28:06.572
<i>I have some stories</i>
<i>you might get a kick out of.</i>

1:28:06.656 --> 1:28:10.576
[chuckling]

1:28:10.660 --> 1:28:15.164
<i>But I am just enjoying</i>
<i>the process.</i>

1:28:15.248 --> 1:28:16.582
<i>You may too.</i>

1:28:21.838 --> 1:28:23.881
<i>Whatever you do,</i>

1:28:23.965 --> 1:28:29.804
<i>I just want you to know</i>
<i>that I love you.</i>

1:28:29.887 --> 1:28:33.433
<i>And planet Earth has got</i>
<i>a few more rotations in it.</i>

1:28:38.813 --> 1:28:41.399
<i>Oh, and also...</i>

1:28:41.482 --> 1:28:44.402
<i>there's a really wonky pipe</i>
<i>under the bathroom sink.</i>

1:28:44.485 --> 1:28:48.197
<i>Get Frank to help you</i>
<i>with that before I forget.</i>

1:28:48.281 --> 1:28:50.491
<i>You don't need</i>
<i>that kind of drama.</i>

1:28:51.409 --> 1:28:54.245
[light music playing]

1:29:10.845 --> 1:29:13.681
[instrumental music playing]
